I started this reflection cuz I was led to do research into better helps stats.  I see hella therapists, influencers and celebs promote better help and I wonder what’s the compensation and also who of the promoters actually uses that platform

There was a sense of urgency that didn’t feel emotionally sustainable for me. I recognize that better help is a different platform for therapists and clients certainly financially…but the amount of time per coin received didn’t add up on the platform I used.

I did not like text based therapy on talkspace. I provide a portal for clients to check in in between sessions but nothing to the scale that was on talkspace. 

I had great client matches and we did great work but
Texting is a way to stay present in the moment, to digitally journal and release but we can also engage in that behavior mindlessly and may not feel better after (trial and error)

If a person is in high distress…processing via text or phone might help but it likely may not help because when in crisis we don’t have access to our reasoning skills and that’s what we would tap into while typing

I think that some people are better candidates for texted based therapy than others. There is a level of urgency that comes with text but it blurs the line of what therapy is because there are no quick fixes
I think text based mental health apps are a nice first step in the door of therapy. I think texting helps to break the ice.

The last day to enroll in health insurance is 12/15/2021 

The process is daunting and my only tip is go for the plan with the lowest deductible. how much you pay a month does not equal full coverage even though common sense would suggest that.

When we react to anger …it’s hard to find what the primary emotions were and where we felt it in our body. Having that information can be so helpful in getting what we really need and communicating what we really need to express. 5

Anger is a high energy emotion and experience It can trigger a fight/flight response Bc of the flood of stress hormones. Sometimes when we are angry we say or do things that can harm us, others or our environment. Sometimes anger occurs bc we first felt hurt or misunderstood etc4

In conclusion please do what you need to do to care for yourself. I promise you that type of energy is reward and amplified. I know it’s so much to get done, and capitalism is a bitch and everyone needs you but YOU NEED YOU.
I learned that I walk bold and fearless when I am protecting and pouring into other people and that I can apply that same energy to myself. That’s pretty cool
I learned that I always have time. There is no race to get to anywhere or do anything. My life is perfectly timed.
I learned that nature and sunlight are nonnegotiable aspects of my well being and trying to thrive without enough of either is harmful and unrealistic
I learned that scared money really don’t make no money.
I learned more about Rejection Sensitivity and how to better navigate through My own experience with it.
I learned that I really enjoy my own company and that there is so much to learn and do with myself and the way I was living and working wasn’t allowing me real and purposeful alone time

I learned that because of my identities, I bring something unique to my loved ones and clients (another type of loved ones). My lived experiences have given me the language to connect with and put words to experiences that people have when they are still in search for them

I learned that my childhood wounds and identity based trauma was negatively impacting me as a clinician and entrepreneur. On the surface it looked good- always training always reading always stretching but it was because I masking feeling of not being GOOD ENOUGH

I learned how important friendship and community is to me. The way I was working and surviving was slowly chippin away my capacity to connect with, talk to, share space with my tribe! The life I quit my job to access I still wasn’t living.
I learned how to rest.  I learned that i did not know to rest and therefore hadn’t rested in years.
